Chris Natt.label: Chris Natt
Chris Natt.description:
Christopher William "Chris" Natt is a former Australian politician and Australian rules footballer with Port Adelaide Football Club.
A ruckman, Natt played 216 games for Port Adelaide between 1972 and 1983. Wikipedia

Jerry Dolan.label: Jerry Dolan
Jerry Dolan.description: John "Jerry" Dolan was an Australian rules footballer and coach in the West Australian Football League before becoming a politician. He played for as well as coached East Fremantle and was also a coach at East Perth. Wikipedia

Darrel Baldock.label: Darrel Baldock
Darrel Baldock.description: Darrel John Baldock AM, commonly nicknamed "The Doc" and "Mr Magic", was an Australian rules football player, coach, and state politician. In 1966 he captained the St Kilda Football Club to its first, and to date only, premiership. Wikipedia

John Devine (Australian rules footballer.label: John Devine
John Devine (Australian rules footballer.description: John Herbert Devine is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the Victorian Football League during the 1960s, and Tasmanian Football League side North Hobart between 1967 and 1974. Wikipedia

Neil Trezise.label: Neil Trezise
Neil Trezise.description: Neil Benjamin "Nipper" Trezise was an footballer in the VFL and Australian Labor Party politician, of Cornish descent. Wikipedia

Alan Arthur.label: Alan Arthur
Alan Arthur.description: Alan Arthur was an Australian rules footballer who played thirty games for Essendon in 1928 and 1930 in the Victorian Football League. Wikipedia

Andrew McLeod.label: Andrew McLeod
Andrew McLeod.description: Andrew Luke McLeod is a former Australian rules footballer for the Adelaide Football Club. He is the games record holder for Adelaide, having played 340 games. Wikipedia

Alan Obst.label: Alan Obst
Alan Obst.description: Alan Obst is an Australian rules football player who played for North Melbourne in the Australian Football League and Central District in the South Australian National Football League. Wikipedia

Anthony Alexander Forrest.label: Anthony Alexander Forrest
Anthony Alexander Forrest.description: Anthony Alexander Forrest was an Australian rules footballer and soldier who was killed in the Second Boer War. Wikipedia

Barry Standfield.label: Barry Standfield
Barry Standfield.description: Barry Standfield is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray and Adelaide in the Australian Football League during the 1990s. Wikipedia

Bill J. Jones.label: Bill J. Jones Attorney At Law, P.A.

Bruce Reid, Sr..label: Bruce Reid, Sr.
Bruce Reid, Sr..description:
Bruce Reid is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray in the Victorian Football League.
Reid, a Romsey recruit, played 17 of a possible 19 games in the 1949 VFL season. Wikipedia

Clancy Rudeforth.label: Clancy Rudeforth
Clancy Rudeforth.description: Clancy Alexander Rudeforth is a former Australian rules footballer who played for the Claremont Football Club in the West Australian Football League, captaining the side from 2009 to 2011. Wikipedia

Bo Nixon.label: Bo Nixon
Bo Nixon.description: Bowman "Bo" Nixon is a former college captain of Assumption College, Kilmore and Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood and Hawthorn in the Australian Football League. Wikipedia

Col Thornton.label: Col Thornton
Col Thornton.description:
Col Thornton is a former Australian rules footballer who played with North Melbourne and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League.
Thornton was a follower, recruited to North Melbourne from Kensington and Coburg Amateurs. Wikipedia

Darren Carlson.label: Darren Carlson
Darren Carlson.description: Darren Graham Carlson is a former Australian rules footballer who played with the Brisbane Bears in the Victorian/Australian Football League. Wikipedia

Darren Millane.label: Darren Millane
Darren Millane.description: Darren "Pants" Millane was an Australian rules football player in the VFL/AFL for the Collingwood Football Club between 1984 and 1991. Wikipedia

Fred Wooller.label: Fred Wooller
Fred Wooller.description:
Fred Wooller is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the VFL.
Recruited from Bacchus Marsh, Wooller started his career as a full forward and topped Geelong's goalkicking with ... Wikipedia

Gordon Hocking.label: Gordon Hocking
Gordon Hocking.description:
Gordon Hocking was an Australian rules footballer who played for Collingwood in the VFL.
Hocking was primarily a knock ruckman but could also play most positions around the ground. Wikipedia

Glenn Nugent.label: Glenn Nugent
Glenn Nugent.description: Glenn Nugent is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Hawthorn and St Kilda in the Australian Football League during the 1990s. Wikipedia

Jarrad Sundqvist.label: Jarrad Sundqvist
Jarrad Sundqvist.description:
Jarrad Sundqvist is an Australian rules footballer who played for Sydney between 2002 and 2003.
He was drafted in the 2000 AFL Draft with the 54th selection from the Glenelg Football Club in the South Australian National Football League. Wikipedia

Darren Denneman.label: Darren Denneman
Darren Denneman.description:
Darren Denneman is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong and the Sydney Swans in the Victorian/Australian Football League.
Denneman was recruited locally by Geelong, from Ocean Grove. Wikipedia

Jack Newnes (Australian footballer).label: Jack Newnes
Jack Newnes (Australian footballer).description:
Jack Newnes is a professional Australian rules football player at the St Kilda Football Club.
Newnes was recruited with pick 37 in the 2011 National Draft, having played as a winger for the Northern Knights in the TAC Cup. Wikipedia

Jay van Berlo.label: Jay van Berlo
Jay van Berlo.description: Jay van Berlo is an Australian rules footballer, who formerly played for the Fremantle Football Club in the Australian Football League. He currently plays for the West Perth Football Club in the West Australian Football League. Wikipedia

Joe Hickey.label: Joe Hickey
Joe Hickey.description:
Joe Hickey is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League.
Hickey was a key forward, recruited to Fitzroy from Shepparton. Wikipedia

John Blair (Australian footballer).label: John Blair
John Blair (Australian footballer).description: John Blair is a former Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne, Fitzroy and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League. He has since become a successful coach in Queensland and is currently senior coach of Morningside. Wikipedia

Jude Bolton.label: Jude Bolton
Jude Bolton.description: Jude Bolton is a retired Australian rules football player who represented the Sydney Swans in the AFL between 1999 and 2013. Bolton currently holds the record for most tackles in a VFL/AFL career. Wikipedia

Kane Munro.label: Kane Munro
Kane Munro.description:
Kane Munro is an Australian rules footballer who played with the West Coast Eagles in the Australian Football League.
Munro grew up in Walpeup but completed his schooling in Bendigo, where he played for the Pioneers. Wikipedia

Max Evans (Australian footballer).label: Max Evans
Max Evans (Australian footballer).description:
Max Evans was an Australian rules footballer who played with Richmond in the Victorian Football League.
Evans played beside his elder brother Ron at Richmond in 1947 and 1948, after coming to the club from Richmond United. Wikipedia

Martin Heffernan.label: Martin Heffernan
Martin Heffernan.description:
Martin Heffernan is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong and the Brisbane Bears in the Australian Football League.
Originally from Terang, Heffernan played his three games for Geelong midway through the 1992 AFL season. Wikipedia

Nicholas Heyne.label: Nicholas Heyne
Nicholas Heyne.description: Nicholas Heyne is an Australian rules footballer presently at the Carlton Football Club in the Australian Football League. Wikipedia

Scott Reed (Australian rules footballer).label: Scott Reed
Scott Reed (Australian rules footballer).description: Scott Reed is an Australian rules footballer currently playing for Collingwood Football Club in the AFL. He plays as a tall forward and was drafted to Collingwood with the 78th selection in the 2009 rookie draft. Wikipedia

Stephen Anderson (Australian footballer).label: Stephen Anderson
Stephen Anderson (Australian footballer).description: Stephen Anderson is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Australian Football League. Wikipedia

Tyson Goldsack.label: Tyson Goldsack
Tyson Goldsack.description: Tyson Goldsack is a professional Australian rules football player currently playing with the Collingwood Football Club in the Australian Football League. Wikipedia

Wade Chapman.label: Wade Chapman
Wade Chapman.description: Wade Chapman is a former Australian rules footballer who played for the Sydney Swans in the Australian Football League during the 1990s. Wikipedia

Terry Waites.label: Terry Waite
Terry Waites.description:
Terry Waite CBE is an English humanitarian and author, famous as a hostage in Lebanon 1987-91.
Waite was the Assistant for Anglican Communion Affairs for the then Archbishop of Canterbury, Robert Runcie, in the 1980s. Wikipedia

Tony Micale.label: Tony Micale
Tony Micale.description: Anthony Claude "Tony" Micale is an Australian rules football coach and former player. He is the current coach of the East Perth Football Club. Wikipedia

Wayne Campbell.label: Wayne Campbell
Wayne Campbell.description: Wayne Campbell is a retired Australian rules football player and administrator for the Richmond Football Club in the AFL. He also had assistant coaching roles at the Western Bulldogs for two years. Wikipedia

Anthony Mellington.label: Anthony Mellington
Anthony Mellington.description:
Anthony Mellington is an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy and North Melbourne in the Australian Football League.
After being picked up in the 1995 Pre-Season Draft, Mellington made six AFL appearances in his first year at Fitzroy. Wikipedia

Don Grossman.label: Don Grossman
Don Grossman.description:
Donald Clarence "Don" Grossman was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne in the Victorian Football League.
A Port Melbourne recruit, Grossman started his VFL career in 1940. Wikipedia
Don Grossman.Born: December 27, 1920 (age 93), Brunswick, City of Moreland, Australia

Heath Culpitt.label: Heath Culpitt
Heath Culpitt.description: Heath Culpitt is an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Australian Football League. Wikipedia

Gerard FitzGerald.label: Gerard FitzGerald
Gerard FitzGerald.description: Gerard FitzGerald is a former Australian rules footballer who played for Geelong in the Victorian Football League and has also had a successful career as a coach. Wikipedia

Josh Mellington.label: Josh Mellington
Josh Mellington.description:
Josh Mellington is an Australian rules footballer with the Fremantle Football Club, in the Australian Football League.
Originally from Benalla, Mellington played junior football for the Murray Bushrangers in the TAC Cup. Wikipedia

Alan Thaw.label: Alan Thaw
Alan Thaw.description:
Alan Thaw was an Australian rules footballer who played for Essendon in the VFL during the late 1940s and early 1950s.
Recruited locally, Thaw was a back pocket in Essendon's 1949 premiership side. Wikipedia

Allan Ruthven.label: Allan Ruthven
Allan Ruthven.description: Allan Ruthven was an Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League. He played his entire 222 game career with Fitzroy. In 1950, Ruthven won the prestigious Brownlow medal. Wikipedia

Ben Davies (Australian footballer).label: Ben Davies
Ben Davies (Australian footballer).description:
Benjamin "Ben" Davies is an Australian rules footballer.
From Williamstown, Davies played in the TAC Cup for the Western Jets. Wikipedia

David Smith (sportsman).label: David Smith
David Smith (sportsman).description: David Bertram Miller Smith was an Australian sportsman. His father was a champion Australian rules footballer for Carlton when Carlton was still in the Victorian Football Association competition. Wikipedia

Doug Wade.label: Doug Wade
Doug Wade.description:
Douglas Graeme "Doug" Wade is a former Australian rules footballer who played for the Geelong Football Club and North Melbourne Football Club.
He was the League's leading goal scorer on four occasions from 1962 until 1974. Wikipedia

Col Austen.label: Col Austen
Col Austen.description: Colin 'Col' Austen was an Australian rules footballer who played for the Hawthorn Football Club in the VFL from 1941 to 1943 and then again from 1946 to 1949. He then played for the Richmond Football Club from 1950 to 1952. Wikipedia

Geoff Leek.label: Geoff Leek
Geoff Leek.description: Geoff Leek was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the VFL from 1951 to 1962. Wikipedia

Ian McLean.label: Ian McLean
Ian McLean.description:
Ian McLean was an Australian rules football player in the Victorian Football League, .
Ian McLean played in Melbourne premiership teams in 1955, 1957 and 1959, and well as the runner-up side of 1954. Wikipedia

George Young (Australian rules footballe.label: George Young
George Young (Australian rules footballe.description: George Alfred Young is a former Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League and Subiaco in the West Australian National Football League during the 1970s. Wikipedia

John Law (Australian rules footballer).label: John Law
John Law (Australian rules footballer).description:
John Law is a former Australian rules footballer who played for North Melbourne during the 1980s.
Law was a half back flanker and captained North Melbourne in both 1988 and 1989. Wikipedia

Joe Misiti.label: Joe Misiti
Joe Misiti.description: "Smokin" Joe Misiti is a former Australian rules football player of Italian descent who played for the Essendon Football Club. Wikipedia

Luke Darcy.label: Luke Darcy
Luke Darcy.description: Luke Darcy is a former Australian rules footballer who played with the Western Bulldogs in the Australian Football League and now works for the Seven Network and Triple M covering the AFL. Wikipedia

Michael Wilson (footballer).label: Michael Wilson
Michael Wilson (footballer).description: Michael Robert Wilson is a former professional Australian rules footballer who played for Port Adelaide Football Club in the Australian Football League and the South Australian National Football League Wikipedia

Nick Smith (footballer born 1984).label: Nick Smith
Nick Smith (footballer born 1984).description: Nicholas "Nick" Smith is an Australian rules footballer with the Box Hill Hawks of the Victorian Football League. Previously, Smith played for the Melbourne Football Club in the Australian Football League. Wikipedia

Clive Waterhouse.label: Clive Waterhouse
Clive Waterhouse.description: Clive Waterhouse is a former Australian rules footballer. He played in the Australian Football League for the Fremantle Football Club as a half-forward flanker. Wikipedia

Danny Stevens (Australian footballer).label: Danny Stevens
Danny Stevens (Australian footballer).description: Daniel "Danny" Stevens is a former Australian rules footballer who played with North Melbourne in the Australian Football League during the 1990s. Wikipedia

Paul Harding (Australian rules footballe.label: Paul Harding
Paul Harding (Australian rules footballe.description:
Paul Harding is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Hawthorn, St Kilda and West Coast in the VFL/AFL.
Paul was a great player for East Fremantle football club, and is remembered at many junior clubs. Wikipedia

Peter Sartori.label: Peter Sartori
Peter Sartori.description: Peter David Sartori is a former Australian rules football player who played for the Carlton Football Club and the Fitzroy Football Club in the AFL and Swan Districts Football Club in the WAFL throughout the mid to late 1980s and early 1990s. Wikipedia

Peter Vardy (footballer).label: Peter Vardy
Peter Vardy (footballer).description:
Peter Vardy is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Adelaide and Melbourne in the AFL.
A small forward, Vardy started his career at Adelaide where he was an AFL Rising Star nominee in 1997. Wikipedia
